  "nursesNote": "OCD involves obsessions (unwanted, intrusive thoughts that cause anxiety) and compulsions (rituals done to relieve that anxiety). The patient usually knows the behavior is excessive but cannot stop alone. At first the nurse allows time for rituals and never shames or punishes the patient, then helps gradually limit them as anxiety eases. Because rituals consume time, the nurse watches basic needs (skin from washing, eating, and rest), teaches other coping skills, and supports treatment with SSRIs and exposure (ERP) therapy.",
  "providerOrders": [
    "Allow time for rituals at first; do not stop them abruptly",
    "Never shame or punish the patient for rituals",
    "Gradually help limit rituals as anxiety decreases",
    "Protect basic needs: skin, nutrition, and rest",
    "Support SSRIs and exposure therapy"
  ],
